{
  "problem": "A 7700 kg boxcar traveling 14 m/s strikes a second car at rest. The two stick together and move off with a speed of 5.0 m/s. What is the mass of the second car?",
  "source": "Quiz 7 - Problem 1",
  "sourceFile": "sources/Quiz 7 FA25 Solution.docx",
  "chapter": "Quiz 7: Momentum & Collisions",
  "variables": [
    {
      "symbol": "m₁",
      "meaning": "mass of incoming boxcar"
    },
    {
      "symbol": "v₁ᵢ",
      "meaning": "initial speed of boxcar 1"
    },
    {
      "symbol": "m₂",
      "meaning": "mass of second boxcar"
    },
    {
      "symbol": "v₂ᵢ",
      "meaning": "initial speed of boxcar 2"
    },
    {
      "symbol": "v₍f₎",
      "meaning": "common final speed after coupling"
    }
  ],
  "correctFormulas": [
    {
      "name": "Conservation of linear momentum",
      "formula": "m₁ v₁ᵢ + m₂ v₂ᵢ = (m₁ + m₂) v₍f₎"
    }
  ],
  "steps": [
    {
      "explanation": "We will use conservation of linear momentum for this perfectly inelastic collision",
      "notations": "m₁ v₁ᵢ + m₂ v₂ᵢ = (m₁ + m₂) v₍f₎"
    },
    {
      "explanation": "Define the known values from the problem",
      "notations": "m₁ = 7700 kg = 7.70 × 10³ kg, v₁ᵢ = 14 m/s, v₂ᵢ = 0 m/s (at rest), v₍f₎ = 5.0 m/s, m₂ = ?"
    },
    {
      "explanation": "Substitute the known values into the momentum equation, noting that v₂ᵢ = 0",
      "notations": "(7.70 × 10³ kg)(14.0 m/s) + m₂(0) = (7.70 × 10³ kg + m₂)(5.0 m/s)"
    },
    {
      "explanation": "Simplify and expand the equation",
      "notations": "1.078 × 10⁵ kg·m/s = (7.70 × 10³ kg)(5.0 m/s) + m₂(5.0 m/s)"
    },
    {
      "explanation": "Continue simplifying",
      "notations": "1.078 × 10⁵ kg·m/s = 3.85 × 10⁴ kg·m/s + m₂(5.0 m/s)"
    },
    {
      "explanation": "Solve for m₂",
      "notations": "m₂(5.0 m/s) = 1.078 × 10⁵ kg·m/s − 3.85 × 10⁴ kg·m/s = 6.93 × 10⁴ kg·m/s"
    },
    {
      "explanation": "Calculate the final answer",
      "notations": "m₂ = (6.93 × 10⁴ kg·m/s) / (5.0 m/s) = 1.39 × 10⁴ kg"
    }
  ],
  "solution": "m₁ v₁ᵢ + m₂ v₂ᵢ = (m₁ + m₂) v₍f₎\nGiven: m₁ = 7.70 × 10³ kg, v₁ᵢ = 14.0 m/s, v₂ᵢ = 0 m/s, v₍f₎ = 5.0 m/s\n(7.70 × 10³ kg)(14.0 m/s) + m₂(0) = (7.70 × 10³ kg + m₂)(5.0 m/s)\n1.078 × 10⁵ kg·m/s = (7.70 × 10³ kg)(5.0 m/s) + m₂(5.0 m/s)\n1.078 × 10⁵ kg·m/s = 3.85 × 10⁴ kg·m/s + m₂(5.0 m/s)\nm₂(5.0 m/s) = 6.93 × 10⁴ kg·m/s\nm₂ = 1.39 × 10⁴ kg"
}
